    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix ASN.1 Encoding Error in M3AP Decoder XER Printing\n\n### Summary\nThe M3AP decoder in `m3ap_decode_pdu` function was attempting to perform XER (XML Encoding Rules) printing of decoded PDUs before verifying that the ASN.1 decoding operation was successful. When malformed or corrupted M3AP messages were received, the `aper_decode` function would fail but leave the PDU structure in an inconsistent state. The subsequent `xer_fprint` call would then attempt to encode this malformed structure, resulting in ASN.1 encoding errors and potential crashes during debugging sessions with XER printing enabled.\n\nThis issue manifested as segmentation faults when `asn1_xer_print` was set to 1 and the gNB received invalid M3AP messages from the MCE. The problem was particularly evident during M3 setup procedures when testing with non-compliant or fuzzed M3AP implementations.\n\nThe fix reorders the decoding logic to check the return code from `aper_decode` before attempting any XER printing operations, preventing attempts to encode potentially corrupted data structures.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/M3AP/m3ap_decoder.c`: Moved XER printing block to occur after ASN.1 decoding success check\n"
}